A = \int_{0}^{x_Q} (x^2 - (mx + c)) \, dx
\]","explanation":"Setting up the integral to find the area."},{"output":"Assume the line passes through the origin and point Q, simplifying the line equation to \( y = mx \).","explanation":"Simplifying assumptions based on typical line behavior."},{"output":"The area becomes:
